{"history":[{"role":"user","content":"Who can get Carer Payment?","timestamp":"2026-02-23T02:17:58.607Z"},{"role":"assistant","content":"To be eligible for Carer Payment, both you and the person you provide care for must meet specific criteria:\n\n1. **You (the carer)** must:\n   - Be providing constant care to someone who has a physical, intellectual, or psychiatric disability, or to an adult who is frail aged.\n   - Provide care for a significant amount of time daily, which is roughly equivalent to a normal working day.\n   - Not be receiving a Department of Veterans’ Affairs (DVA) payment that affects your eligibility.\n\n2. **The pe","timestamp":"2026-02-23T02:17:58.607Z"}],"memories":[{"id":"mem-6751f114-1771813078607","query":"Who can get Carer Payment?","answer":"To be eligible for Carer Payment, both you and the person you provide care for must meet specific criteria:\n\n1. **You (the carer)** must:\n   - Be providing constant care to someone who has a physical, intellectual, or psychiatric disability, or to an adult who is frail aged.\n   - Provide care for a significant amount of time daily, which is roughly equivalent to a normal working day.\n   - Not be receiving a Department of Veterans’ Affairs (DVA) payment that affects your eligibility.\n\n2. **The person you care for** must:\n   - Require care for at least 6 months or be at the end of their life.\n   - Be assessed as needing care by a medical professional.\n\nAdditionally, there are no income or assets tests for Carer Payment, meaning your financial situation does not affect your eligibility for this payment [Source 1][Source 3][Source 8].","sources":[{"file":"general/getting-payment-if-youre-carer.md","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.2652490486915918},{"file":"payments/carer-payment.md","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.28592580595349726},{"file":"documents/sites--default--files--2025-12--co029-2601.pdf.md","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.32371584644523177},{"file":"allowances/carer-allow